fields.name: Nike  Air Mag sneakers
fields.slogan: Nearly fifty years after its conception in 1971, Nike’s iconic Swoosh logo remains unchanged, showcasing a prevalent and pioneering symbol for the brand.
fields.description: Nearly fifty years after its conception in 1971, Nike’s iconic Swoosh logo remains unchanged, showcasing a prevalent and pioneering symbol for the brand. Perhaps the most sought-after sneaker of all time, the Nike Mag from Back to the Future Part II was released in 2011 via limited eBay auctions to support the Michael J. Fox Foundation. The pair feature a round toe, a flat rubber sole, a signature Nike swoosh, a mid-calf length, a branded ankle strap and light-up detailing. These styles are supplied by a premium sneaker and street wear marketplace. Stocking only the most sought-after footwear and clothing, they source and curate some of the most hard-to-find items from around the world.
